\begin_layout Itemize
Exploring magnetic reconnection in 3D (Aug'22 - Present)
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Advisor: Prof.
 Pallavi Bhat
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

We study 
\series bold
magnetic reconnection
\series default
 of two 
\series bold
antiparallel flux tubes
\series default
 in 3D using MHD.
 To this end, 
\series bold
numerical experiments
\series default
 are performed using the Dedalus-Code.
 The ultimate aim here is to develop a better understanding of reconnection
 in 3D and draw analogies and differences between 3D reconnection and 2D
 reconnection.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Mapping radio polarisation and the underlying magnetic fields using invariants
 (Jan'23 - Present)
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Advisor: Prof.
 Rajaram Nityananda
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The 
\series bold
magnetic field
\series default
 in the 
\series bold
accretion disc
\series default
 around the black holes M87 and Sgr A* has been mapped by full polarisation
 radio interferometry by the EHT collaboration but is still subject to some
 uncertainties.
 A recently proposed set of 
\series bold
invariants
\series default
 which cancel antenna based errors (arXiv 2108.11400) is a promising tool
 to improve this process.
 The aim of this project is to study the connection between these invariants
 and the magnetic field geometry using simulations.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
MHD and the Tearing Mode instability (Jan'22 - Jun'22) 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Advisor: Prof.
 Pallavi Bhat
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

I read about and worked through basic 
\series bold
magnetohydrodynamics
\series default
, the 
\series bold
reduced-MHD model
\series default
 and the classical 
\series bold
tearing mode instability
\series default
.
 Pencil-Code was used to perform simulations of a tearing unstable 
\series bold
current sheet
\series default
.
 The dependence of the growth rate of the instability on simulation parameters
 was studied.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

